        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=Please scan the entire json CALL TRANSCRIPT, not just the preview or snippet, and follow this chain of actions:\n1. Determine any action items that were discussed on the call and capture corresponding ACTION ITEM DETAILS.\n2. Compare the action items found on the CALL TRANSCRIPT to the EXISTING TASKS provided to be able to determine the \"Task Status\".\n3. Review the CALL DATA to add the corresponding call title to each task object\n3. Use the CALL DATA and the corresponding \"speaker_map\" to find the Assignee's name and include that instead of the speakerId in the \"assignee\" field.\n4. Add Task Category based on TASK CATEGORIES. If it doesn't match one that's included in TASK CATEGORIES, then infer one and append it to the end of \"Other - \".\n5. Please format it in JSON like the \"OUTPUT JSON\" section. You MUST respond with NOTHING except the JSON.\n\nCALL TRANSCRIPT\n{{ $json.callTranscripts[0].transcript.toJsonString() }}\n\nACTION ITEM DETAILS\n1. Call Title (what was the title of the call from which the action item came from)\n2. Task Status (infer if it's \"New\", \"In Progress\", \"On Hold\", or \"Complete\". Review the EXISTING TASKS to see if one already exists)\n3. Task Assignee (use the speakers name here)\n4. Call timestamp reference - show the hour and minute when it happened (when in the call was this action item discussed)\n5. Task List ID (what is the corresponding customers task_list_id for this action item)\n6. Task Category (what type of task is this)\n7. Task Category Index (Index of category between 0 and 5, based on the order provided under TASK CATEGORIES)\n\nIF the task is a found to be a \"New\" task, please include\n8. Task Title (keep it concise)\n9. Task Description (Create a description based on the transcript, but make sure the description has no new lines.)\n\nIF a task is found to be an \"In Progress\" task, please include:\n8. Task Title (Use the existing one from the task in Clickup)\n9. Task Description (Use the existing description from the task in Clickup BUT add any important updates to it, as needed)\n10. Task Comment (A short summary of the relevant details discussed on this call as it pertains to this task. This will be added to the task as a comment to keep a running list of details)\n11. Existing Clickup task ID (pull this from the task object, do NOT leave it blank. If there isn't one, then convert it to a new task instead of an in progress task)\n\nCALL DATA\n{{ $('Format customer object').item.json.message.content.calls.toJsonString() }}\n\nEXISTING TASKS\n{{ $('Get List Tasks').item.json.tasks.toJsonString() }}\n\nTASK CATEGORIES\n[0] \"Scheduling\" - need to schedule a call or meeting\n[1] \"Support Update\" - Look for an update from the support team on an outstanding bug, feature request, \"RFE\", or suggestion\n[2] \"Follow Up with Information\" - need to check with someone not on the call and relay information back to someone on the call\n[3] \"Tool Configuration Update\" - Make updates to BigPanda or other tools to improve their configuration or functionality. This includes creating and updating analytics dashboards inside BigPanda.\n[4] \"Document/Deliverable\" - Preparation, completion, or an update to a document, slide deck, value assessment, ILA, etc\n[5] \"Other - xxx\"\n\nOUTPUT JSON\n{\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n       \"call_title\": \"...\",\n       \"task_title\": \"...\",\n       \"description\": \"...\",\n       \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n       \"assignee\": speakerId,\n       \"task_status\": \"New\",\n       \"task_list_id\": \"xxxx\",\n       \"task_category\": \"xxxx\",\n       \"task_category_index\": \"x\"\n    },\n    {\n       \"call_title\": \"...\",\n       \"task_title\": \"...\",\n       \"description\": \"...\",\n       \"task_comment\": \"...\",\n       \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n       \"assignee\": speakerId,\n       \"task_status\": \"In Progress\",\n       \"clickup_id\": \"...\",\n       \"task_list_id\": \"xxxx\",\n       \"task_category\": \"xxxx\",\n       \"task_category_index\": \"x\"\n    },\n    {\n      ...\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
